<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 24 at 5:57PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Snow showers with minor additional accumulation expected across
portions of Southwest Montana into this evening...
Snow showers have been heavy at times across Southwest Montana
late this afternoon, but they should start to diminish after 7 pm.
Snowfall on roads across the area, including portions of
Interstates 15 and 90, and over Big Hole Pass, will make those
roads icy and possibly snow covered in spots. Visibility will also
be reduced to less than one mile in spots.
Take it slow on the roads through this evening, and be prepared
for rapidly changing road and visibility conditions.</description>
